title: For Sale/Trade:  Vektor CP1
postcontent: I have a very rare Vektor CP1 9mm, seldom seen stainless slide, with original hard case and paperwork, 3 magazines. These guns have a sordid history. They were imported from South Africa. Only 2000 were imported before the recall, and Vektor offered $100 over list price to return them. Estimates of less than 200 still remaining in the US. The recall was because they have no firing pin block safety and if dropped they could discharge. Please google this. The Vektor is gas operated, a gas port under the barrel. Hammer fired, internal hammer, polygonal rifling, Imported under the Clinton gun ban with 10 round magazines. There are two of these for sale on Gunbroker right now, they both have black slides not stainless and both are over $900. Asking $1000. Trade or partial trade.
